<subSubSection id="4FF0884673E1EA33F96BB79517CF40CE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="08EB8BD56D10144D466EE514C92F5303" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6279DB77F9F1F1CB7F3A452B47B318CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Legs reddish brown; tibia of middle leg with apical spine; tarsomere I modified. Sides of ventrite V strongly shortened in males.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFF197C165E5CA19E8D36F85AC291E7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="B9311D880BDDE2025AC34E3EB37CD015" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA027FA1B3320965F69E447080F52BB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Length 4.6-5.5 mm, width 2.4-2.9 mm. Body color (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="16BA7B043639F82865BBBF385A6AE765" captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figure 27. Habitus of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. and P. semifulva (Jacoby) A P. formosanensis sp. nov., female, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D P. semifulva, from Taiwan, female, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545557" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">27A-C</figureCitation>
) reddish brown; head black but antennae dark brown. Eyes small, interocular space 2.62-2.69 
<normalizedToken id="9BCAC3E120D7689859994F4211458F9C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of eye. Antennae filiform in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5E95A0D31410D654FBC1083082D8FAB5" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28A</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.6: 0.8: 0.8: 0.6: 0.7: 0.6: 0.6: 0.6: 0.6: 0.8, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 2.8: 1.9: 2.5: 2.4: 2.0: 2.2: 2.0: 1.9: 1.9: 2.0: 2.4; similar in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0290C2BAA7141E828EED5597B41843F0" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28B</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.5: 0.7: 0.6: 0.6: 0.6: 0.6: 0.6: 0.6: 0.5: 0.7, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 3.2: 2.0: 2.4: 2.2: 1.9: 2.0: 1.9: 1.7: 1.7: 1.6: 2.2. Pronotum and elytra convex. Pronotum 2.1-2.2 
<normalizedToken id="B129A926B59830330E86299FBA11A2AA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
wider than long, disc with dense, extremely coarse punctures and extremely short pubescence, with transverse ridge near apical margin deflexed near antero-lateral corners, with median longitudinal and lateral depressions; lateral margins moderately rounded, apical margin slightly concave, basal margin straight; anterior and posterior setiferous punctures slightly erect. Elytra elongate and broad, parallel-sided, 1.4-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="6E0082CC6DD64BC1C366D5CAD74B4C3A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; disc with dense, extremely coarse punctures and extremely short pubescence. Apical spur of tibia of middle leg slender (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3DB8E79799E505025124A1A25C987000" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28G</figureCitation>
), tarsomere I axe-shaped in lateral view, with narrow basal part and expanded apical 2/3, posterior angles of expanded part narrowly rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8A472F88DD0AB16E774EC7B1B2506345" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28M</figureCitation>
) in males. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C4FB17A1CF77E3820681C35BE07020E7" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28C-E</figureCitation>
) extremely asymmetric in dorsal view, inner margin of right side expending at apical 1/3, covering right side of ostium, lateral margin of right side expanding downwards, with a notch at middle; inner margin of left side expanding inwards at basal 2/5 and apical 2/5; primary endophallic sclerite elongate, several fine teeth on apex. Sclerotized gonocoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0E717F01849F0F78B0EEB297115A956D" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28J</figureCitation>
) transverse, both gonocoxae separated, with several long setae near apices. Ventrite VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D08BA80812CB994746AE696FDB03B8A6" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28H</figureCitation>
) transverse; disc with dense, long setae along apical margin; spiculum short. Receptacle of spermatheca (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4C1D31DC9CDB9964E0CEFB049FCD3233" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta formosanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, left-side view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, right-side view G apex of tibia of middle leg, male H abdominal ventrite VIII I spermatheca J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, male L abdominal ventrite V, female M tarsi of middle leg, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">28I</figureCitation>
) slightly swollen; pump short and strongly curved; sclerotized proximal spermathecal duct wide and short. Apical margin of abdominal ventrite V slightly concave medially, with deep triangular depression at middle in males, sides of abdominal ventrite V shortened, sides of basal margin of abdominal ventrite IV expanding downwards in males (Fig. 
